SIMPLE: mastership
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mastership
<hw>Mas"ter*ship</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The state or
office of a master.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Mastery; dominion; superior skill;
superiority.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Where noble youths for <qex>mastership</qex> should strive.</q>
<rj><qau>Driden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Chief work; masterpiece.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>An ironical title of respect.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>How now, seignior Launce! what news with your
<qex>mastership</qex>?</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mastersinger</ent>⟦br⟧
